<section id="mobile-push-android-virtual-device" role="topic">
    <sectioninfo>
        <abstract>
            <para>Describes how to set up a device to install the push messaging-enabled &AMHlong;
                quickstart app in Android Studio.</para>
        </abstract>
    </sectioninfo>
    <title id="mobile-push-android-virtual-device.title">Create an Android Virtual Device</title>
    <para>To send push notifications from Amazon Pinpoint to an Android app, you must install the app on an
        Android device. As a proof of concept, you can use a virtual device. This topic describes
        how to create a virtual device in Android Studio. If you have a physical Android device and
        know how to install apps onto it using Android Studio, you can skip this step. </para>
    <para>This topic helps you create a virtual device of type Nexus 6 phone with Lollipop API Level
        22 x86 Android 5.1, but the &AMHlong; quickstart app is not limited to this device. You can
        use any device that uses Android OS 4.0.3 (IceCreamSandwich) API Level 15 or higher.</para>
    <procedure>
        <title>To create a virtual device with Android Studio</title>
        <step>
            <para>Open Android Studio.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>From the <guilabel>Tools</guilabel> menu, choose <guilabel>Android</guilabel>, and
                then choose <guilabel>AVD Manager</guilabel>.</para>
            <informalfigure>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-avd-manager.png"
                            format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </informalfigure>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>On the <guilabel>Your Virtual Devices</guilabel> page, choose <guilabel>Create
                    Virtual Device</guilabel>.</para>
            <informalfigure>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-create.png"
                            format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </informalfigure>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>On the <guilabel>Select Hardware</guilabel> page, choose <guilabel>Nexus
                    6</guilabel>, and then choose <guilabel>Next</guilabel>.</para>
            <informalfigure>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-hardware.png"
                            format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </informalfigure>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>On the <guilabel>System Image</guilabel> page, choose the setup with
                    <guilabel>Release name</guilabel> Lollipop, <guilabel>API Level</guilabel> 22,
                    <guilabel>ABI</guilabel> x86, and <guilabel>Target</guilabel> Android 5.1 (with
                Google APIs), and then choose <guilabel>Next</guilabel>.</para>
            <informalfigure>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-image.png"
                            format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </informalfigure>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>On the <guilabel>Android Virtual Device</guilabel> page, choose
                    <guilabel>Finish</guilabel>.</para>
            <informalfigure>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-finish.png"
                            format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </informalfigure>
        </step>
        <step>
            <para>To enable Android Studio to install an app on the virtual device, go to the
                    <guilabel>Tools</guilabel> menu, choose <guilabel>Android</guilabel>, and then
                choose <guilabel>Enable ADB Integration</guilabel>.</para>
            <informalfigure>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata
                            fileref="&url-doc-domain;images/en_us/mobile-shared/mobile-push/push-android-amh-quickstart-virtual-device-enable-adb.png"
                            format="PNG" scale="65"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </informalfigure>
        </step>
    </procedure>
